shared_text:
Elka Hristova was live.
November 9, 2018 at 9:12 AM ¬∑

We were at Create Academy,a K-6 charter school in Phoenix, Arizona, as part of the DanceSport Education program in partnership with the world-class ballroom dance professionals from Imperial Ballroom Dance Company - Artem Plakhotnyi, Rose Dimov, leading the Demo class, assisted by Donovan Dominguez, Oleh Teleha and Michele Brecker! THANK YOU!!!

We are so excited, we start regular classes at the school on Monday. We will be teaching the students in grades 2 and 4. They will learn to ballroom dance as part of their regular school day. We are fundraising through the 8th Annual Masquerade Ball Gala to be able to make this a school-wide program! We are excited to work with Create Academy's school leadership, who have recognized the many benefits ballroom dancing brings to their students!

post_text: It's Chameleon Carnival time again! Come enjoy the enrollment carnival at Create Academy, one of Phoenix's unique arts integration elementary charter schools. Children and families can get to know our school, while enjoying fun projects, Improv classes, facepainting, inflatable water slides, food, and much more! Our talented teachers will be available to share more of our program and our staff will provide tours and be available for questions. FREE EVENT!

Create Academy is hosting its last Learning Lab this Saturday 7/7 for KG-6th grade.
This is a free event, from 10-11am, here on campus. We will have Storytime for the little ones and science activities for the upper elementary grades.
It will be a great opportunity to visit the school, meet the teachers and staff, and have a good time. Snacks will be provided! The learning Lab will be open to everyone, so feel free to bring siblings, cousins, neighbors and friends.

shared_text:
PLAY added 139 new photos to the album: Valentine's Day Market ‚Äî at Create Academy.
February 10, 2018 ¬∑ Phoenix, AZ ¬∑

We had a wonderful time at Create Academy's first annual Valentine's Day Market.

The local community event encourages all to participate and enjoy the fun.

PLAY held yoga sessions and valentine's day card making.

Everyone there was able to help paint the newest mural on the school's campus, jump-into a hula hoop challenge, and even plant some seed to start your own garden.

Thank you for bringing the community together and spreading kindness.

DanceSport Education is feeling excited at Create Academy.
February 6, 2018 at 11:27 AM ¬∑ Phoenix, AZ ¬∑

Thanks to the generous donations from our Gala sponsors, we are able to sustain and increase the number of children in our DanceSport Education program. Even better, we are able to reduce class size to improve instruction!

@ Create Academy, we will continue the program with the 3rd grade students! We are so excited to share the joy of ballroom dance with the 1st graders, too!!!

We bring ballroom dance directly to the students-in their schools, at their classrooms! www.dancesported.org
